			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To Sarnath and woot spelled the name right the first time. Anyway, i wouldnt blame you for thinking that a wizard cant solo either all that well or at all in higher lvls, especially if your friends that play wizards tell you so. I must admit its tough to solo at the low to mid lvls using root to keep a mob off ya. People thinking wizards cant solo later on is a common misconception, made even by wizards of around the 55th lvl. They arent the best soloers but can solo mobs that are blue maybe even up till 60, although i dont think id recommend that they do so. As for necro pets taunting a mob off a ranger id believe that = ), a monk, i play one and i can take mobs off a taunting warrior as well as a taunting pet, but id say its still possible. A mage pet can taunt well with spells, well id say only earth pets since root is the ultimate taunt if the &quot;rooter&quot; is in melee range.<BR>
<BR>
Back on topic, iv'e heard rumors of the bp nerf as well as the healing agro &quot;being corrected&quot;, that i would hope to see in the somewhat near future, but im not counting on it as it is only heresay as of yet. Id think if this would happen that VI would regain some respect they had before. I also believe you would see a million clerics on again. I do not believe that, if they indeed &quot;corrected&quot; this horrible mistake, that the healing agro in specific would be, so to speak, back to normal. I would imagine they would increase the agro from what it was back before any of this cleric ~cough~ &quot;nerf&quot; ~cough~, however it would obviously be decreased (maybe greatly) from what it is at the moment. Lets all cross our fingers and hope so, it would add more fun to the game which is what most of us play EQ for. I would also like to add that it was rumored this nerf was over two main issues. The plvling of chars by clerics, and to &quot;screw&quot; FoH of Veeshans main tactics over. In respect to FoH, it may seem that as soon as they clear Sleeper's Tomb (most definetly not something easy to do) they decide to increase healing agro. In what little respect i have left for VI, it may take time to plan and think about these changes before they occur, however its not impossible to target main guilds or groups of players and nerf clerics to punish them in a way, and can also be done so in a short period of time (hmmm emergency patch). Although im not saying the cleric nerf was an emergency patch.<BR>
<BR>
What i have yet to see is how any recent nerfs targeted towards clerics have any positive effect on the EQ community. Maybe to make a druid more powerful, although druids are indeed part of the percentage arguing / debating (whatever pretty name you wish to call it) over such recent nerfs. Once more ...<BR>
<BR>
All i can say...<BR>
<BR>
Good luck with hell, and good luck with cash flow ~grin~
