				I would just like to make a couple of points that pertain to these so called nerf issues.<BR>
<BR>
Common sense tells me that Verant does not want to upset people in general, they are smart enough to know that customers will leave if things get out of control.<BR>
What I cant understand is how come people cannot just send in their concerns without threats and the (Im going to quit) comments. Funny thing is I see these same people saying it again 2 months later.<BR>
If they came out with a bp that gave the whole party Invul. would that make these certain people happy. Verant tries different items, quests , etc to keep people interested and some times they dont work out. SHOULD they STOP adding more content.<BR>
THen there would be no reason for them to have to make changes. If there was a bp that gave the whole group invul permanantly would that be ok to. I truly believe that Verant listens to players who send in factual information,tests,etc but not to those who just spam and make threats every single time they perceive some class or item is being nerfed.<BR>
I have played Eq for 2 years, and many many other computer games, my god before Eq I was buying 3 games a month. I could be a EB store.<BR>
You know what the minute I got to the point where <BR>
I figured the AI out or the game just got to easy, I was off to buy another.<BR>
I am one who appreciates balance as long as Verant listens to us when we make FACTUAL, comments,test,or supporting evidence of some kind.<BR>
How many things as Verant changed due to customer requests..MANY MANY MANY. <BR>
For those of you who come to these boards and complain, and threaten and etc , I hope you do move on to another game , but you will be back.<BR>
And for those who come in with good solid info, <BR>
Thank you for helping the Eq player.<BR>
I have no problem with people being passionate, even aggravated as long as their comments are productive in some way.<BR>
Thank you for you time.
